<h1>Problem 1671 - 2023 IMO, P3 of 6, AN</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>For each integer \(k\geq 2\), determine all infinite sequences of positive integers \(a_1\), \(a_2\), \(\ldots\) for which there exists a polynomial \(P\) of the form\[P(x)=x^k+c_{k-1}x^{k-1}+\dots + c_1 x+c_0,\]where \(c_0\), \(c_1\), \dots, \(c_{k-1}\) are non-negative integers, such that\[P(a_n)=a_{n+1}a_{n+2}\cdots a_{n+k}\]for every integer \(n\geq 1\).</p>
